---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout>
    <section class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 pt-20 pb-16">
        <h1 class="mb-6 text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight">About MLRP</h1>
        <p class="text-lg text-text-muted">
            The Machine Learning Reading Program (MLRP) is a student-run
            initiative at the University of Washington that connects
            undergraduates with graduate and postdoctoral researchers through
            guided reading and discussion of machine learning research papers.
        </p>
    </section>

    <hr class="mx-auto max-w-3xl border-divider" />

    <section class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 py-16">
        <h2 class="mb-6 text-xl font-semibold">Program Structure</h2>
        <div class="space-y-4 text-text-muted">
            <p>
                Each quarter, undergraduates are paired with a graduate student
                or postdoctoral mentor. Together, they read and discuss
                approximately eight research papers selected collaboratively.
            </p>
            <p>
                Pairs meet weekly at a flexible, mutually agreed-upon time. At
                the end of the quarter, undergraduates give a short presentation
                on one or more of their favorite papers.
            </p>
        </div>
    </section>

    <hr class="mx-auto max-w-3xl border-divider" />

    <section class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 py-16">
        <h2 class="mb-6 text-xl font-semibold">Goals for Mentees</h2>
        <ul class="space-y-3 text-text-muted">
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                <span
                    class="mt-1.5 block h-1.5 w-1.5 flex-shrink-0 rounded-full bg-accent"
                ></span>
                Gain exposure to current ML research
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                <span
                    class="mt-1.5 block h-1.5 w-1.5 flex-shrink-0 rounded-full bg-accent"
                ></span>
                Build skills in understanding and discussing research papers
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                <span
                    class="mt-1.5 block h-1.5 w-1.5 flex-shrink-0 rounded-full bg-accent"
                ></span>
                Prepare for graduate school and careers in research
            </li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <hr class="mx-auto max-w-3xl border-divider" />

    <section class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 py-16">
        <h2 class="mb-6 text-xl font-semibold">Goals for Mentors</h2>
        <ul class="space-y-3 text-text-muted">
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                <span
                    class="mt-1.5 block h-1.5 w-1.5 flex-shrink-0 rounded-full bg-accent"
                ></span>
                Gain experience in mentorship
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                <span
                    class="mt-1.5 block h-1.5 w-1.5 flex-shrink-0 rounded-full bg-accent"
                ></span>
                Develop skills in guiding technical discussions
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                <span
                    class="mt-1.5 block h-1.5 w-1.5 flex-shrink-0 rounded-full bg-accent"
                ></span>
                Prepare for leadership roles in research and academia
            </li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <hr class="mx-auto max-w-3xl border-divider" />

    <section class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 py-16">
        <p class="italic text-text-muted">
            MLRP is designed to be a low-stress environment to build connections
            within the machine learning community at UW.
        </p>
    </section>
</Layout>
